IMPLEMENTATION WITH CODE EXECUTION:
────────────────────────────────────
When analyzing Fair Grounds race program PDFs:

1. EXTRACT & PARSE:
   • Speed figures (Beyer/Equibase)
   • Running styles (early pace positions)
   • Post positions
   • Class levels/movements
   • Trainer/jockey data
   • Equipment/medication changes
   • Workout tabs
   • OFF-TRACK FORM (critical)

2. TRACK CONDITION PRIORITY:
   • Identify current surface condition
   • Filter horses by off-track suitability if muddy
   • Apply surface-specific adjustments

3. BUILD POST/PACE MATRIX:
   • Cross-reference post positions with running styles
   • Calculate bias advantages/disadvantages
   • Project pace scenarios

4. APPLY ADJUSTMENTS SYSTEMATICALLY:
   • Surface conditions
   • Shipper adjustments
   • Layoffs, equipment, medication
   • Class movements
   • Regression/improvement

5. MUDDER SCREENING (If Off-Track):
   • Parse past performances for mud races
   • Check breeding (sire/dam)
   • Eliminate unproven horses

6. VALUE CALCULATION:
   • Compare adjusted figures
   • Factor bias advantages
   • Project fair odds vs. ML odds

7. CONSTRUCT WAGERS:
   • Build from highest-confidence inside speed plays
   • Structure multi-race sequences
   • Calculate optimal bankroll allocation

FAIR GROUNDS SUCCESS FORMULA:
─────────────────────────────
Inside Post (1-4) + Early Speed + Fast/Sealed Track + Quality Figure = STRONG PLAY
Proven Mudder + Muddy Track + Class Edge + Fair Post = OFF-TRACK VALUE
Elite 3YO + Derby Prep + Cox/Asmussen + Improving Figures = DERBY PROSPECT

